Leaves on trees, changing colour,
A sight to behold,
Red and yellow, brown and orange,
Like a treasure chest of gold.

Autumn time, with its peculiar personality,
Organic, earthy, weather traits of whimsicality.

Foggy mornings, dark damp nights,
The best time is Autumn,
To see the Northern Lights.

Nice family walks in rustics woods,
Cosy jumpers,
Coats with hoods.

Autumn winds send leaves swirling,
Mini tornado‚Äôs from the ground,
Underfoot, crispy leaves,
love that crunchy sound.

Horse chestnut trees yield Autumn pearls,
Game of conkers,
Played by boys and girls.

All hallows eve, trick or treat,
Pumpkins carved, sweets kids overeat.

November 5th, on muddy parks,
Crackling bonfire,
Fireworks give off sparks.

As clocks go back,
And hedgehogs hibernate,
Starting counting down for Christmas,
I can hardly wait.

